    "pitfalls_to_avoid": [
      "DO NOT attempt a big-bang migration — sequence by priority and use parallel-run with traffic shifting",
      "DO NOT introduce a message broker without idempotency in consumers — at-least-once delivery means duplicate messages are guaranteed",
      "DO NOT split the database before establishing API contracts — you need the API layer first so services have an alternative data path",
      "DO NOT deprecate /everything endpoint before all consumers have migrated — use sunset headers and access logging to track migration",
      "DO NOT use the cron-over-HTTP pattern for any new background jobs — new jobs go directly to the job queue",
      "DO NOT create a shared event schema library that all services depend on — each consumer should own its own deserialization to avoid distributed monolith",
      "DO NOT skip the dual-write phase during database split — cutting over without verification risks data loss"
    ]
  },

